RuleGroup.RuleString: CLERIC_GOOD or CLERIC_NEUTRAL or PALADIN_ANCIENTS or PALADIN_DEVOTION

Text.Value: *The realisation hits you - that stench wasn't the dead. You can sense that the hyena's very flesh is desecrated...*

RuleGroup.RuleString: !(CLERIC_GOOD and CLERIC_NEUTRAL and PALADIN_ANCIENTS and PALADIN_DEVOTION)

Text.Value: *You watch with cold realisation - this isn't the end of one life, but the start of another...*
*Slowly, her broken body starts to calm, to stop its wild contortions. She lies still.*

EditorData.VFXTags: FX_Special [Murat] - Hyena shrieks and starts thrashing around.

Text.Value: *The beautiful broken heap smells oddly enticing. You find you can't resist inhaling her offals.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The hyena is trying to drag herself to the player, but cannot due to the weight in her stomach.

Text.Value: Bless the hyena, trying to purge her body of evil.
What's happening to you? Is there any way I can help?
Show mercy, ending her life swiftly.
No. Come closer - feed the new flesh.

EditorData.NodeContext: in agony, but full of glee as she is torn apart by a creature being born from within

Text.Value: *Whatever horrific creature was growing inside the hyena dies along with her.*
*...Gnolls can spawn from the corpses of dying hyenas.*
Smite the abomination.
Feel its power, the Butcher is hungry. You, me - all meat.

EditorData.NodeContext: rapturous but in agony as chaos magic tears her apart

Text.Value: Can't leave me - new flesh needs to feed.

EditorData.NodeContext: in agony, about to 'become' a gnoll by gruesomely bursting open - still hungry and wants to eat us though

Text.Value: Step back to watch the show.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Character gains advantage on initiative in the following combat.

Text.Value: Hurts... it hur-hur-hur-ha-ha-ha...

EditorData.NodeContext: Pained groan, then attempt to repeat 'hurts' falls away into deranged, pained laughter right before she dies

Text.Value: *Radiant power flows through you as you strike the creature down.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: radiant effect as paladin strikes the hyena - re-using animation from other death-blows in this dialogue if possible

Text.Value: Strike while the beast is vulnerable.
Butcher's stronger than you, meat.

EditorData.NodeContext: rapturous but in agony as chaos magic tears her apart

Text.Value: *Her darling pups will not be of her own species. Gnolls bring forth their iniquitous litter from many corpsed wombs - including hyenas.*
*You engrave her pained mewls upon your heart. Her back arches impossibly - a grace made possible only by it being broken.*
*The creature's eyes roll back in its head - equal parts bliss and agony.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The hyena is trying to drag herself to the player, but cannot due to the weight in her stomach.
EditorData.VFXTags: FX_Special [Murat] - The creature's eyes rolled back in its head. FX_SpeakWithAnimal_Spell

Text.Value: *The hyena moans softly as its body contorts, ribs cracking and flesh tearing.*

EditorData.VFXTags: FX_Special [Murat] - Hyena body contorted, ribs cracking.

Text.Value: Come... see. My flesh becomes new flesh.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The hyena is trying to drag herself to the player, but cannot due to the weight in her stomach.
EditorData.NodeContext: rapture and agony combined - she's dying, but also becoming something new
EditorData.VFXTags: FX_Special [Murat] - The creature's eyes rolled back in its head. FX_SpeakWithAnimal_Spell

Text.Value: *You move quickly, but not quickly enough.*
*The raw hate of life, reared from the miracle of death. A tear almost springs to your eye.*
Yes - come closer. Feed the new flesh.

EditorData.NodeContext: in agony, but full of glee as she is torn apart by a creature being born from within

Text.Value: *You hear what comes next before you see it: the sharp snapping of bones and a yelp of pain as her body starts to twist and undulate.*

EditorData.SFXTags: Snapping of bones and yelp of pain.
EditorData.VFXTags: FX_Special [Murat] - Dying hyena body starting to twist.

Text.Value: Show mercy, ending her life swiftly.
Watch the beast die.
*...Gnolls - vicious, monstrous humanoids - can spawn from the corpses of dying hyenas.*
*The surge of holy power is rebuked, knocking you back.*

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Player is dazed/stunned when combat begins.

Text.Value: *You strike quickly, but not quickly enough. She shrieks, thrashing helplessly.*

EditorData.VFXTags: FX_Special [Murat] - Hyena shrieks and starts thrashing around.

Text.Value: *The beast reeks of brimstone and offal, every breath thick with blood. Almost gagging, you mutter a quiet prayer to your god.*
*The beast reeks of brimstone and offal. Every breath is thick with blood.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The hyena is trying to drag herself to the player, but cannot due to the weight in her stomach.

Text.Value: *Her offals smell irresistible, and while her bloodfeast has filled her, the hyena is not yet sated.*
*Bones snap as the hyena is hollowed from the inside out, forming a vessel for something new.*

EditorData.VFXTags: FX_Special [Murat] - The hyena hollowed from the inside out.

Text.Value: Leave.
Flesh inside is quiet - flesh inside is dead. Murderer.

EditorData.NodeContext: exhausted and accusatory - we just soothed her pain, but she lost her purpose and is dying anyway

Text.Value: Bless the hyena, trying to purge her body of evil.
Destroy the abomination.
Is there any way to stop this?
*As the life fades from her eyes, the gnoll within her dies too, stillborn.*
*Your nostrils fill with the rank smell of death. The hyena has feasted, but looking into her eyes, you know it wasn't enough. She's still hungry.*
*She'd eaten. Feasted. And yet, looking into her eyes, you can see it wasn't enough. She's still hungry.*
Revel in the creature's demonic influence.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Character gains advantage on initiative in the following combat.

Text.Value: *Her belly splits like a rotten fruit, birthing a frenzy of claws and fangs.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: "Her belly split like a rotten fruit, birthing a frenzy of claws and fangs."
EditorData.StateChangeTags: The gnoll is outside the hyana.
EditorData.VFXTags: FX_Special [Murat] - Hyena body splitting open, blood, guts. the Gnoll come from the Hyena.

Text.Value: *You hear what comes next before you see it: the sharp snapping of bones and a yelp of pain as her body starts to twist and undulate.*

EditorData.SFXTags: Snapping of bones and yelp of pain.
EditorData.VFXTags: FX_Special [Murat] - Dying hyena body starting to twist.

Text.Value: There, now, it's all right. It'll be over soon.
Try not to be sick.
Stifle your excitement. This is grotesque.
*You land a swift strike against her skull. She yelps, then goes still.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: [ANIMALS] - Player strikes hyena in the skull, hyena yelps and dies. <Murat>

Synopsis: The player encounters a dying hyena that is about to turn into a gnoll. If they discover this in time, they can try to stop the gnoll from being born. Otherwise, the gnoll is born and attacks the player when the dialogue ends.
